<br>
But even if the admin was a complete moron, Linux is still more stable and secure than your average consumer OS (e.g. Windows XP) for example.<br>
<br>
Obviously if the adminstrators doesn't configure it properly then it will be far easier to hack the system but, you require a fair amount of knowledge to hack a Linux system. Where as people who have been at it a couple of hours could hack your Win32 system with ease.<br>
<br>
NB: I'm referring to a default configurations here, not taking into account firewalls and virus killers etc.<br>
<br>
